  "Idea": "This research proposes 'Modeling the Emotional Transmission Gap Dynamically' (METG-Dyn), a novel framework that extends the static emotional transmission gap into a dynamic, conversation-level phenomenon by capturing how discrepancies between writer-intended and reader-perceived emotions evolve over multi-turn interactions. While existing emotion detection models assume emotional meaning is fixed upon utterance, METG-Dyn posits that emotional interpretation is recursively shaped by prior turns, relational context, and feedback asymmetries. The core innovation lies in combining longitudinal dual-annotation with graph neural networks (GNNs) to model the trajectory of emotional misalignment across dialogue. In METG-Dyn, participants engage in dyadic text-based conversations where, after each utterance, both speakers annotate their own expressive intent (emotion, intensity, valence, arousal) and later, independently, their perceived emotions in the partner’s message. This yields paired time-series data of intent-perception gaps at each turn. We enrich this with speaker-specific metadata (personality traits via BFI-S, cultural background, current affective state) and linguistic features (emotion lexicon, syntactic complexity, hedge use). Using a GNN architecture inspired by COGMEN, we represent each conversation as a dynamic graph where nodes are utterances annotated with intent and perception vectors, and edges encode speaker dependency, temporal sequence, and emotional congruence. The model learns to predict the evolution of the transmission gap over time and identifies critical transition points—such as when low-intensity mismatches escalate into full emotional dissonance. Furthermore, we introduce an intervention module that suggests real-time rephrasings to minimize predicted future gaps, trained via reinforcement learning with human-rated emotional coherence as reward. Applications include emotionally resilient dialogue agents, early warning systems for empathic breakdowns in therapy chats, and fairness-aware AI that adapts to cultural differences in emotional expression. By shifting from isolated texts to dialogic processes, METG-Dyn redefines emotion-aware AI around *relational fidelity*—ensuring sustained emotional alignment across interaction.",
